HEADWORD: Filoplume
<hw>Fil"o*plume</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>filum</ets> a thread <?/ <ets>pluma</ets> a soft feather.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A hairlike feather; a father with a slender
scape and without a web in most or all of its length.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

